20with%20half%20the%20players%20and%20lost%20on%20the%20last%20ball%20with%20a%20four%20of%20a%20flock.%20But%20in%20this%20match%2C%20I%20have%20been%20shown%20a%20total%20superstar%20bowler%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Zaman%20Khan%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F118360-zaman-khan-playerprofile%5C%22%3EZaman%20Khan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20was%20bowling%20very%20well%20even%20in%20high%20pressure.%20Win%20or%20lose%20game.%20It%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20team%2C%20but%20the%20team%20played%20the%20whole%20competition%20despite%20being%20in%20half%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Siddiqui%20in%20a%20post%20on%20Instagram%20in%20Urdu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInshallah%2C%20when%20everyone%20is%20fit%20in%20the%20World%20Cup%2C%20it%20will%20be%20fun%20to%20see%20the%20competitions.%20Allah%20only%20sees%20what%20happens%20with%20intention%20and%20action%20from%20the%20heart.%20Whether%20he%20accepts%20it%20or%20not%2C%20He%20is%20my%20Lord.%20I%20think%20the%20team%20has%20sacrificed%20their%20lives.%20Let's%20encourage%20the%20team%20at%20this%20time%20and%20make%20their%20hearts%20big.%20This%20is%20patriotism.%20Long%20live%20Pakistan.%20(I%20just%20talked%20to%20Babar%2C%20he%20was%20not%20able%20to%20talk.%20I%20told%20him%2C%20'Braves%20live%20or%20learn.'%20Never%20break)%2C%20%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694871060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2F14evcej8_babar-shaheen-afp_625x300_16_September_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fwar-of-words-between-babar-azam-and-shaheen-afridi-after-pakistans-asia-cup-2023-exit-report-4396056%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Babar%20Azam-led%20Pakistan%20cricket%20team%2C%20despite%20a%20good%20start%20to%20the%20Asia%20Cup%202023%2C%20could%20not%20keep%20up%20the%20momentum%20and%20were%20knocked%20out%20of%20the%20Super%204%20stage%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fwar-of-words-between-babar-azam-and-shaheen-afridi-after-pakistans-asia-cup-2023-exit-report-4396056%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fwar-of-words-between-babar-azam-and-shaheen-afridi-after-pakistans-asia-cup-2023-exit-report-4396056%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fwar-of-words-between-babar-azam-and-shaheen-afridi-after-pakistans-asia-cup-2023-exit-report-4396056%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22With%20'A%20Haunting%20in%20Venice'%2C%20the%20Director%20Goes%20in%20More%20for%20Mood%20and%20Atmosphere%20Rather%20Than%20Glamour%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F16171626%2Fimage-1321.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EA%20Haunting%20in%20Venice%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20one%20can%20almost%20immediately%20tell%20that%20director%2Factor%20Kenneth%20Branagh%20intends%20to%20class%20things%20up%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20glossy%20%3Cem%3EMurder%20On%20The%20Orient%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2017)%20and%20star-filled%20%3Cem%3EDeath%20on%20The%20Nile%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022).%20In%20Branagh%E2%80%99s%20third%20outing%20as%20Hercule%20Poirot%2C%20a%20sense%20of%20doom%20hangs%20over%20the%20film%20from%20the%20very%20first%20frame%20%E2%80%93%20a%20distinctly%20Hitchcockian%20visual%20of%20a%20murder%20of%20crows%20%E2%80%93%20after%20which%20a%20visibly%20traumatised%20Poirot%20wakes%20up%20in%20his%20apartment%20in%20Venice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20inspired%20choice%20that%20reveals%20Branagh%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20move%20away%20from%20glamour%20of%20his%20earlier%20films%20is%20the%20presence%20of%20composer%20Hildur%20Gu%C3%B0nad%C3%B3ttir%20%E2%80%93%20best%20known%20for%20%3Cem%3EJoker%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EChernobyl%3C%2Fem%3E%20(both%20released%20in%202019).%20Gu%C3%B0nad%C3%B3ttir%20%E2%80%93%20famous%20for%20her%20unconventional%20scores%20that%20convey%20mood%20rather%20than%20leaving%20the%20audience%20with%20%E2%80%98melodic%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98hummable%E2%80%99%20pieces%20%E2%80%93%20is%20an%20excellent%20choice%20to%20communicate%20the%20sense%20that%20something%E2%80%99s%20not%20quite%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpening%20in%201947%20in%20the%20city%20of%20canals%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20shown%20Poirot%20in%20self-imposed%20retirement.%20He%20has%20a%20bodyguard%20(Riccardo%20Scarmaccio)%20who%20ensures%20the%20detective%20can%20enjoy%20being%20retired%2C%20without%20being%20hounded%20by%20potential%20clients%20who%20queue%20up%20in%20front%20of%20his%20house%20every%20other%20day.%20He%E2%80%99s%20visited%20by%20a%20friend%20%E2%80%93%20a%20mystery%20writer%20called%20Ariadne%20Oliver%20(Tina%20Fey)%20%E2%80%93%20who%20as%20Poirot%20puts%20it%2C%20is%20there%20to%20seduce%20him%20with%20a%20case%20by%20provoking%20his%20curiosity.%20Oliver%20tells%20Poirot%20about%20a%20psychic%20named%20Joyce%20Reynolds%20(Michelle%20Yeoh)%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20only%20recently%20released%20from%20prison%20%E2%80%93%20claiming%20to%20be%20a%20medium%20who%20talks%20to%20people%20who%20have%20passed%20on.%20As%20a%20mystery%20writer%2C%20Oliver%20tells%20Poirot%20how%20she%E2%80%99s%20uncovered%20nearly%20all%20the%20fraudulent%20ways%20of%20Reynolds%E2%80%99%20kind%2C%20except%20for%20Reynolds%20herself.%20Oliver%20convinces%20Poirot%20to%20participate%20in%20a%20seance%20on%20Halloween%20night%20to%20uncover%20Reynolds%E2%80%99%20tricks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20Christie%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EHallowe%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Een%20Party%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20fine%20set-up.%20What%20better%20way%20to%20start%20off%20a%20story%20about%20(probable)%20spirits%20and%20ghosts%20than%20to%20have%20one%20of%20the%20most%20staunch%20rationalists%20in%20the%20room%3F%20Branagh%20treats%20%3Cem%3EA%20Haunting%20in%20Venice%3C%2Fem%3E%20like%20a%20horror%20film.%20There%20are%20carefully%20crafted%20scares%20that%20are%20almost%20guaranteed%20to%20provoke%20a%20few%20screams%20in%20the%20theatre.%20Reynolds%E2%80%99%20character%20is%20introduced%20wearing%20a%20Noh%20mask%20%E2%80%93%20which%20goes%20on%20to%20become%20an%20important%20plot-point%20in%20the%20film.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20Poirot%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20disdain%20for%20the%20likes%20of%20Reynolds%20cannot%20be%20contained%20%E2%80%93%20is%20confronted%20by%20the%20psychic%20about%20knowing%20the%20curse%20of%20being%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgifted%E2%80%9D%20one.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20tremendous%20moment%20between%20towerings%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20Branagh%20and%20Yeoh%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20film%20hints%20that%20everything%20can%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20reasonable%20explanation.%20It%E2%80%99s%20one%20of%20the%20finest%20attributes%20of%20the%20film%20%E2%80%93%20which%20merely%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20go%20about%20debunking%20the%20myths%20like%20a%20checklist%20%E2%80%93%20but%20also%20acknowledges%20that%20even%20the%20wisest%20among%20us%20can%E2%80%99t%20categorically%20explain%20every%20occurrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whodunit%20skeleton%20has%20gotten%20a%20reinvention%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20most%20famously%20in%20Rian%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EKnives%20Out%3C%2Fem%3E%20films.%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20films%20almost%20feel%20like%20feature-length%20winks%20at%20audiences%2C%20given%20how%20the%20films%20use%20the%20tropes%20of%20the%20genre%2C%20suffuse%20them%20with%20%E2%80%98topicality%E2%80%99%20and%20place%20dramatic%20actors%20(to%20varying%20degrees)%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20most%20bizarre%20set-ups.%20And%20his%20films%20are%20undeniably%20sexy%20%E2%80%93%20with%20superb%20performances%2C%20and%20dazzling%20visual%20language%20%E2%80%93%20which%20could%20easily%20spawn%20replicas.%20Thankfully%2C%20Branagh%20goes%20in%20the%20opposite%20direction%20and%20treats%20his%20whodunit%20like%20a%20genre%20film%20rather%20than%20as%20a%20blockbuster.%20The%20result%20is%2C%20the%20visual%20language%20of%20a%20moody%20A24%20film%20(the%20studio%20behind%20the%20excellent%20%3Cem%3ETalk%20To%20Me%20%3C%2Fem%3Erecently)%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20standard%2020th%20Century%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gothic%20medieval%20architecture%2C%20Gu%C3%B0nad%C3%B3ttir%E2%80%99s%20foreboding%20score%2C%20Branagh%E2%80%99s%20most%20low-key%20ensemble%20%E2%80%93%20including%20Jamie%20Dornan%2C%20Kelly%20Reilly%2C%20Camille%20Cottin%2C%20Kyle%20Allen%2C%20apart%20from%20Fey%20and%20Yeoh%20%E2%80%93%20adds%20up%20to%20a%20mystery%20that%20ties%20up%20its%20loose%20ends%20neatly%2C%20perhaps%20too%20neatly%2C%20by%20the%20end%2C%20but%20one%20that%20also%20references%20old-school%20satisfaction%20of%20mysteries.%20Branagh%E2%80%99s%20ostentatious%20Belgian%20accent%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20get%20in%20the%20way%20of%20a%20haunted%20performance%20of%20a%20man%20%E2%80%93%20who%20knows%20everything%20there%20is%20to%20know%20%E2%80%93%20and%20yet%20seems%20to%20be%20grappling%20with%20the%20unknowables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBranagh%E2%80%99s%20film%20even%20while%20flirting%20with%20the%20supernatural%20roots%20its%20horrors%20in%20the%20plausible.%20The%20palazzo%2C%20where%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20film%20unfolds%2C%20is%20said%20to%20have%20been%20an%20erstwhile%20children%E2%80%99s%20hospital%20%E2%80%93%20where%20doctors%20and%20nurses%20are%20believed%20to%20have%20locked%20and%20abandoned%20their%20patients%2C%20during%20the%20plague.%20A%20character%20recounts%20the%20terror%20he%20witnessed%20in%20the%20Second%20World%20War%20%E2%80%93%20leaving%20them%20with%20a%20permanent%20case%20of%20%E2%80%9CBattle%20Fever%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20making%20everyone%20jumpy%20during%20social%20gatherings%20and%20lash%20out%20during%20the%20most%20unexpected%