oint%20that%20the%20Chinese%20state%20and%20communist%20party%20work%20together%20in%20this%20endeavour.%20What%20makes%20this%20book%20worth%20reading%20is%20the%20matter-of-fact%20way%20in%20which%20the%20author%20acknowledges%20that%20the%20United%20States%20(and%20more%20generally%20the%20Western%20world)%20was%20deeply%20complicit%20in%20creating%20the%20conditions%20for%20this%20to%20happen.%20America%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98unilateral%20neo-liberalism%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20Allen%E2%80%99s%20view%2C%20is%20what%20created%20the%20ideal%20environment%20for%20China%20to%20weaponise%20its%20economy%20for%20geo-political%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20260px)%2085vw%2C%20260px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F16174945%2Fbeijing-rules-original-imagkkbxcaw7hk2e.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22260%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F16174945%2Fbeijing-rules-original-imagkkbxcaw7hk2e.jpg%20650w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F16174945%2Fbeijing-rules-original-imagkkbxcaw7hk2e-195x300.jpg%20195w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673330%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBeijing%20Rules%3A%20China%E2%80%99s%20Quest%20for%20Global%20Influence%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Bethany%20Allen.%20Publisher%3A%20John%20Murray.%20Photo%3A%20flipkart.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Allen%2C%20the%20ending%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%20was%20the%20moment%20in%20time%20when%20America%20took%20down%20its%20democratic%20guardrails%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20upon%20which%20American%20global%20power%20was%20based.%20Believing%20in%20free-market%20economics%2C%20the%20United%20States%20not%20only%20ended%20meaningful%20policy%20interventions%20in%20the%20domestic%20economy%20but%20also%20allowed%20China%20a%20free%20pass%20into%20global%20trading%20arrangements%20in%20the%20mistaken%20belief%20that%20markets%20on%20their%20own%20could%20sustain%20American%20economic%20dominance%20in%20the%20post-Cold%20War%20age.%20One%20of%20the%20principal%20arguments%20in%20the%20book%20is%20that%20the%20West%20suffered%20from%20an%20ideological%20%E2%80%98handicap%E2%80%99%2C%20refusing%20to%20believe%20that%20Chinese%20government%20intervention%20and%20policy%20in%20the%20economy%20might%20actually%20succeed%20in%20making%20China%20a%20competitor%20in%20the%20long%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20equating%20democracy%20with%20free-market%20capitalism%2C%20the%20Americans%20failed%20to%20discern%20that%20China%20could%20build%20state%20capitalism%20that%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20also%20allowed%20its%20authoritarian%20political%20system%20to%20thrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllen%20gives%20interesting%20examples%20of%20how%20this%20blindness%20about%20the%20innate%20superiority%20of%20democracy%20and%20free%20markets%20caused%20the%20Western%20world%20to%20dismiss%20facts%20about%20massive%20Chinese%20governmental%20backing%20for%20Huawei%20which%20allowed%20it%20to%20challenge%20Western%20technological%20dominance%20on%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20and%20to%20ignore%20instances%20of%20Chinese%20pressure%20on%20Western%20corporations%20like%20Zoom%20or%20LinkedIn%20to%20collaborate%20with%20the%20Chinese%20communist%20party%E2%80%99s%20political%20goals%20in%20return%20for%20market%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhow-china-is-shifting-its-foreign-policy-to-counter-the-west%5C%22%3EHow%20China%20Is%20Shifting%20Its%20Foreign%20Policy%20to%20Counter%20the%20West%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20belief%20that%20companies%20have%20a%20moral%20right%20to%20bolster%20their%20profits%20by%20any%20legal%20means%20available%2C%E2%80%9D%20Allen%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9Chas%20also%20contributed%20to%20decades%20of%20successful%20lobbying%20against%20government%20restrictions%20on%20trade%20with%20China.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20coercive%20tactics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllen%20is%20not%20shy%20about%20calling%20out%20the%20West%20for%20permitting%20China%20to%20leverage%20its%20expanding%20domestic%20market%20for%20geopolitical%20advantage%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20use%20market-denial%20means%20to%20serve%20the%20Communist%20Party%E2%80%99s%20interests.%20The%20author%20is%20disingenuous%20when%20she%20claims%20that%20the%20United%20States%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20used%20sanctions%20to%20uphold%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20international%20system%20rather%20than%20in%20pursuit%20of%20their%20raw%20national%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20does%20not%20detract%20from%20the%20book%E2%80%99s%20key%20argument%20that%20America%E2%80%99s%20neoliberal%20approach%20permitted%20the%20Chinese%20to%20use%20economic%20coercion%20to%20ensure%20that%20Hollywood%20did%20not%20produce%20films%20that%20portrayed%20China%20in%20a%20poor%20light%2C%20to%20pressurise%20countries%20like%20Norway%20and%20the%20Philippines%20when%20they%20were%20seen%20as%20acting%20against%20China%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98core%E2%80%99%20interests%2C%20and%20to%20dangle%20China%E2%80%99s%20market%20potential%20in%20front%20of%20Google%2C%20Apple%20and%20LinkedIn%20as%20a%20trade-off%20for%20them%20agreeing%20to%20censorship%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chapter%20titled%20%E2%80%98Zooming%20In%E2%80%99%20is%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20a%20chilling%20account%20of%20how%20the%20Chinese%20were%20able%20to%20manipulate%20employees%20of%20Zoom%20in%20China%20in%20order%20to%20shut%20down%20virtual%20meetings%20that%20were%20critical%20of%20Chinese%20politics%2C%20even%20when%20the%20participants%20were%20located%20outside%20China%2C%20mostly%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20company%20itself%20was%20apparently%20complicit%20in%20granting%20Chinese%20security%20services%20special%20access%20to%20its%20systems%20in%20return%20for%20being%20allowed%20to%20operate%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20growing%20influence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEqually%20revealing%20are%20other%20chapters%20in%20the%20book%20that%20talk%20of%20Chinese%20influence%20operations%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20other%20countries%20through%20entities%20like%20the%20United%20Front%20Work%20Department%20or%20the%20International%20Department%20of%20the%20communist%20party%2C%20which%20have%20no%20counterpart%20organisations%20in%20democratic%20systems%20and%2C%20hence%2C%20sail%20below%20the%20radar%20of%20Western%20national%20security%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chapter%20titled%20%E2%80%98Spies%20and%20Sister%20Cities%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20brilliant%20account%20of%20how%20Chinese%20intelligence%20turned%20a%20Western%20Cold%20War%20tool%20%E2%80%93%20establishing%20sister-city%20relationships%20with%20cities%20behind%20the%20Iron%20Curtain%20in%20order%20to%20bypass%20Communist%20governments%20%E2%80%93%20into%20a%20weapon%20to%20subvert%20America.%20Christine%20Fang%2C%20a%20suspected%20intelligence%20operative%2C%20was%20able%20to%20target%20(and%2C%20in%20some%20instances%2C%20honey-trap)%20US%20politicians%20and%20influence%20local%20governments%20by%20using%20the%20easy%20access%20provided%20by%20sister-city%20programmes%20the%20US%20had%20initiated%20with%20China%2C%20as%20a%20geopolitical%20tool%20to%20influence%20how%20Americans%20thought%20about%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202005%2C%20according%20to%20Allen%2C%20China%20had%201%2C247%20sister%20city%20relationships%20with%20129%20countries%20(including%20India).%20Allen%20writes%20about%20the%20way%20in%20which%20the%20Chinese%20offered%20several%20sister-city%20proposals%20to%20the%20Awami%20League%20government%20of%20Bangladesh%20during%20the%20COVID%20crisis%20in%20return%20for%20pandemic%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F09085822%2F24939411081_39dd945cb2_c.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22799%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F09085822%2F24939411081_39dd945cb2_c.jpg%20799w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F09085822%2F24939411081_39dd945cb2_c-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-643312%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20researchers%20working%20in%20a%20lab%20in%20China.%20Photo%3A%20Can%20Pac%20Swire%2FFlickr%20(CC%20BY-NC%202.0)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EKey%20chapters%20in%20Allen%E2%80%99s%20book%20relate%20to%20how%20the%20pandemic%20showed%20both%20the%20best%20qualities%20of%20China%20%E2%80%93%20in%20terms%20of%20its%20assistance%20to%20others%20less%20fortunate%20%E2%80%93%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Communist%20Party%E2%80%99s%20worst%20impulses.%20Her%20point%20is%20that%20the%20pandemic%20has%20exposed%20the%20Chinese%20game%20and%20come%20at%20a%20reputational%20cost%20that%20the%20Communist%20Party%20seems%20to%20have%20underestimated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chapter%20titled%20%E2%80%98The%20Global%20Rush%20for%20Masks%E2%80%99%20highlights%20how%20China%E2%80%99s%20attempts%20to%20corner%20PPE%20kits%20worldwide%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20including%20by%20using%20its%20diaspora%2C%20and%20the%20supply%20chain%20shocks%20that%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20endured%20across%20businesses%2C%20has%20had%20a%20powerful%20and%20lasting%20impact%20on%20both%20the%20US%20and%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllen%20says%20that%20the%20US%20might%20have%20finally%20turned%20the%20corner%20with%20policymakers%20demonstrating%20a%20new%20willingness%20to%20use%20the%20levers%20of%20government%20to%20protect%20the%20economy.%20She%20credits%20Trump%20with%20this%20turnabout%2C%20and%20at%20places%2C%20the%20author%20seems%20to%20show%20a%20Republican%20bias.%20The%20pivot%20to%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20credited%20to%20Trump%20rather%20than%20to%20Obama%2C%20marks%2C%20as%20Allen%20describes%20it%2C%20a%20substantive%20and%20comprehensive%20departure%20from%20the%20decades-long%20engagement%20era.%20Events%20in%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20Chinese%20behaviour%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20supply%20chain%20shocks%2C%20the%20experience%20of%20American%20allies%20have%2C%20Allen%20claims%2C%20all%20brought%20about%20a%20structural%20shift%20in%20American%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllen%20applauds%20the%20measures%20taken%20by%20the%20Biden%20Administration%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20very%20good%20start%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20says%20that%20the%20more%20difficult%20tasks%20of%20reforming%20or%20replacing%20compromised%20international%20bodies%20like%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organisation%20are%20still%20needed%20to%20fully%20insulate%20Western%20economic%20interests%20from%20geopolitical%20risk%20associated%20with%20China.%20She%20also%20hammers%20home%20the%20argument%20that%20putting%20new%20guardrails%20on%20Chinese%20economic%20behaviour%20that%20has%20geopolitical%20motives%2C%20will%20require%20legislative%20action.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20legal%20force%20should%20be%20deployed%20in%20defence%20of%20Western%20liberal%20values%20and%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20chapter%20outlines%20steps%20that%20America%20might%20take%20to%20build%20a%20democratic%20response%20to%20Chinese%20economic%20statecraft%20that%20will%20help%20preserve%20national%20security%20and%20American%20economic%20predominance.%20It%20appears%20to%20be%20written%20with%20an%20eye%20to%20the%20next%20administration%20in%202025.%20Allen%E2%80%99s%20ideas%20range%20from%20strengthening%20public%20oversight%20over%20social%20media%20platforms%20and%20strengthening%20labour%20unions%20against%20predatory%20big%20business%2C%20to%20creating%20mechanisms%20that%20will%20legally%20prohibit%20transacting%20business%20with%20entities%20of%20authoritarian%20governments.%20Many%20of%20these%20ideas%2C%20such%20as%20diversifying%20supply%20chain%20risks%20and%20fire-proofing%20the%20American%20economy%20by%20erecting%20new%20legal%20and%20institutional%20mechanisms%2C%20have%20been%20touted%20in%20the%20past.%20However%2C%20Allen%20does%20not%20answer%20the%20question%20about%20whether%20the%20American%20political%20system%20is%20capable%2C%20or%20even%20desirous%2C%20of%20fundamental%20reforms.%20Nor%20does%20it%20deal%20with%20how%20American%20corporations%20can%20be%20persuaded%20to%20give%20up%20profit%20for%20the%20intangible%20and%20undefinable%20objective%20of%20serving%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20smorgasbord%20of%20Allen%E2%80%99s%20suggestions%20suggests%20that%20while%20America%20has%20identified%20that%20it%20has%20a%20problem%20with%20China%2C%20it%20has%20no%20clear%20idea%20of%20what%20to%20do%20about%20it.%20Nor%20is%20it%20clear%20whether%20the%20guardrails%20that%20the%20author%20is%20advocating%20are%20China-specific%20and%2C%20if%20so%2C%20how%20they%20can%20be%20legally%20enacted%20and%20enforced.%20The%20book%20itself%2C%20however%2C%20is%20definitely%20worth%20reading%20for%20the%20wealth%20of%20detail%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20Chinese%20economic%20coercion%20and%20because%20it%20paints%20a%20full%20picture%20of%20the%20myriad%20challenges%20confronting%20democratic%20governments%20in%20tackling%20China%2C%20both%20geo-politically%20and%20economically%2C%20as%20it%20moves%20closer%20to%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVijay%20Gokhale%20is%20a%20former%20foreign%20secretary%20of%20India%20and%20a%20former%20ambassador%20to%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694868651000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc