2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fmillions-under-storm-watches-and-warnings-as-hurricane-lee-bears-down-on-new-england-and-canada%2Farticleshow%2F103713053.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fmillions-under-storm-watches-and-warnings-as-hurricane-lee-bears-down-on-new-england-and-canada%2Famp_articleshow%2F103713053.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fmillions-under-storm-watches-and-warnings-as-hurricane-lee-bears-down-on-new-england-and-canada%2Famp_articleshow%2F103713053.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Conserving%20Modern%20Architecture%20Has%20Become%20Nearly%20Impossible%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F03203111%2FSVP-stadium.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpenguin.co.in%2Fbook%2Ftemple-lamp%2F%5C%22%3EMirza%20Ghalib%E2%80%99s%20verse%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EMy%20heart%20boils%20in%20the%20clamour%20of%20discontent%2F%20This%20voiceless%20bubble%20augurs%20a%20storm%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20best%20captures%20the%20current%20mood%20of%20Indian%20architects%20horrified%20by%20the%20quick%20loss%20of%20significant%20modern%20buildings.%20The%20iconic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fdelhi%2Fdelhis-iconic-hall-of-nations-demolished-4626629%2F%5C%22%3EHall%20of%20Nations%20in%20Delhi%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20pulled%20down%20six%20years%20ago.%20Last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fiim-ahmedabads-historic-dorms-to-be-history-with-u-turn-on-demolition-historian-slams-move%2F1211091%2F%5C%22%3EIIM%20Ahmedabad%20decided%20to%20demolish%20about%2014%20buildings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20mostly%20dormitories%2C%20on%20their%20internationally%20renowned%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArchitecturally%20significant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fgoa%2Fportion-of-iconic-kala-academy-of-goa-collapses%2Farticleshow%2F101826999.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3EKala%20Academy%20in%20Goa%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20faces%20a%20threat%2C%20and%20recently%2C%20a%20part%20of%20the%20structure%20collapsed.%20Recent%20reports%20indicate%20that%20the%20impressive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahmedabadmirror.com%2Fend-of-an-era%2F81863126.html%5C%22%3ESardar%20Patel%20Stadium%20in%20Ahmedabad%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20described%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wmf.org%2Fproject%2Fsardar-vallabhbhai-patel-stadium%5C%22%3EWorld%20Monuments%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20representation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98experimental%20spirit%20that%20characterised%20India%E2%80%99s%20post-independence%20period%2C%E2%80%99%20will%20be%20pulled%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArchitects%20lament%20these%20losses%20since%20they%20embody%20the%20best%20values%20of%20their%20practice%20and%20tell%20stories%20of%20progress%2C%20invention%2C%20and%20architecture%E2%80%99s%20contribution%20to%20the%20country.%20Without%20these%20exemplar%20structures%2C%20they%20are%20worried%20that%20the%20already%20beleaguered%20profession%20would%20be%20further%20impoverished.%20The%20sense%20of%20loss%20is%20acute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20no%20storm%20brewing%20because%20of%20these%20demolitions.%20At%20the%20most%2C%20a%20few%20mild%20online%20protests%20have%20happened.%20People%20have%20given%20up%2C%20and%20the%20hope%20of%20protection%20for%20what%20is%20left%20of%20modern%20architecture%20seems%20to%20be%20receding.%20For%20good%20reasons%2C%20many%20blame%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20apathy%20and%20private%20owners%E2%80%99%20greed%20for%20the%20present%20state.%20However%2C%20they%20alone%20are%20not%20the%20reasons%20for%20this%20disquieting%20condition.%20Other%20equally%20critical%20factors%20include%20the%20narrow%20definition%20of%20heritage%20and%20architects%E2%80%99%20failure%20to%20articulate%20modern%20architecture%E2%80%99s%20values.%20Without%20examining%20them%2C%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20solution%20would%20not%20be%20fruitful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20key%20factors%20have%20put%20modern%20architecture%20in%20this%20unenvious%20spot.%20First%20is%20placing%20age%20as%20the%20primary%20determinant%20of%20what%20constitutes%20heritage.%20Second%2C%20the%20Indian%20architecture%20discourse%20casts%20suspicion%20on%20modern%20architecture%20as%20non-indigenous.%20Third%20is%20modern%20architecture%E2%80%99s%20preoccupation%20with%20the%20new%20and%20denial%20of%20history%20to%20establish%20its%20relevance.%20Fourth%20is%20the%20conflict%20between%20the%20use%20and%20exchange%20values%20of%20the%20buildings%2C%20which%20has%20recently%20intensified%20since%20a%20premium%20is%20placed%20on%20the%20land%2C%20not%20the%20building%20that%20stands%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAge%20has%20been%20a%20key%20determinant%20in%20declaring%20a%20structure%20as%20heritage.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiaculture.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Facts_rules%2FTheAncientMonumentsandArchaeologicalSitesandRemainsAct1958_12.03.2018.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20Ancient%20Monuments%20and%20Archaeological%20Sites%20and%20Remains%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India%20enunciates%20that%20only%20structures%20that%20have%20survived%20100%20years%20qualify%20as%20heritage%20and%20can%20receive%20legal%20protection.%20Longevity%20is%20the%20key%20determining%20test.%20The%20assumption%20is%20that%20one%20needs%20sufficient%20years%20to%20assess%20the%20significance%20of%20structures%2C%20and%20hence%2C%20the%20older%2C%20the%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F16142547%2FJudge_Business_School_Cambridge-300x225.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F16142547%2FJudge_Business_School_Cambridge-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F16142547%2FJudge_Business_School_Cambridge.jpg%20400w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673303%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22225%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Judge%20Business%20School.%20Photo%3A%20Public%20domain%2FWikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20understandable%2C%20using%20the%20longevity%20test%20as%20a%20filter%20to%20manage%20a%20large%20inventory%20of%20competing%20old%20structures%20for%20heritage%20status%20is%20not%20useful.%20Repeatedly%2C%20this%20has%20been%20challenged%2C%20and%20exceptions%20have%20been%20made.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20where%20the%20threshold%20value%20is%2050%20years%2C%C2%A0%20the%20multi-storied%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2Fpdf%2F26502502.pdf%5C%22%3ECiticorp%20Center%20was%20designated%20as%20a%20landmark%20in%202016%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20though%20it%20was%20only%2038%20years%20old.%20In%20England%2C%20the%20threshold%20age%20is%2030%20years%2C%20which%20has%20helped%20designate%20outstanding%20buildings%20completed%20as%20recently%20as%201996%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistoricengland.org.uk%2Fwhats-new%2Fnews%2Fpost-modern-buildings-listed%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20Judge%20Business%20School%2C%20Cambridge%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Eas%20heritage%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENothing%20comparable%20has%20happened%20in%20India.%20There%20was%20an%20opportunity%20to%20unambiguously%20recognise%20modern%20buildings%20as%20heritage%20when%20a%20few%20states%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F14461%2F1%2F2001-9.pdf%5C%22%3EWest%20Bengal%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Facts_states%2Ftamil-nadu%2F2012%2F2012TN24.pdf%5C%22%3ETamil%20Nadu%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20enacted%20heritage%20legislation%20to%20care%20for%20non-monumental%20structures.%20However%2C%20even%20state-level%20efforts%20have%20mostly%20identified%20colonial%20and%20a%20few%20pre-colonial%20buildings%20as%20heritage.%20Focusing%20on%20the%20public%20value%20of%20modern%20architecture%20is%20the%20way%20to%20correct%20this.%20For%20it%20to%20happen%2C%20changes%20must%20begin%20within%20architectural%20discourse%20and%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20modern%20architecture%20in%20India%20is%20viewed%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suspicion%20that%20modern%20buildings%20are%20not%20indigenous%20must%20be%20challenged%20and%20corrected.%20Modern%20architecture%20in%20India%20is%20viewed%20as%20a%20shadow%20of%20European%20and%20American%20architecture.%20It%20is%20criticised%20for%20showing%20faith%20in%20modernist%20doctrines%20such%20as%20functionalist%20planning%20and%20a%20faithful%20following%20left%20behind%20by%20architects%20such%20as%C2%A0%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.co.in%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FAfter_the_Masters%2FMPlPAAAAMAAJ%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26bsq%3DVikram%2BBhatt%2Band%2BPeter%2BScriver%2C%2BAfter%2Bthe%2BMasters%26dq%3DVikram%2BBhatt%2Band%2BPeter%2BScriver%2C%2BAfter%2Bthe%2BMasters%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%3ELe%20Corbusier%20and%20Louis%20Kahn%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.orientblackswan.com%2Fdetails%3Fid%3D9788178243054%5C%22%3EArchitectural%20historians%3C%2Fa%3E%20tend%20to%20portray%20that%20it%20was%20only%20after%20the%201980s%20when%20Indian%20architecture%20engaged%20with%20the%20vernacular%20and%20the%20historical%20as%20a%20redemption.%20It%20is%20only%20in%20recent%20years%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moma.org%2Fmagazine%2Farticles%2F698%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20have%20started%20to%20reassess%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20early%20modern%20architecture%20in%20India%20is%20beginning%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20confident%20expression%20of%20its%20conditions%20and%20an%20emancipatory%20project%20representing%20an%20independent%20country%E2%80%99s%20progressive%20and%20pluralistic%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmitpress.mit.edu%2F9780262534710%2Fbuildings-must-die%2F%5C%22%3EStephen%20Cairns%20and%20Jane%20M.%20Jacobs%2C%20architect%20and%20urban%20studies%20experts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20called%20architects%20%E2%80%98natalists%2C%E2%80%99%20who%20always%20thought%20about%20making%20things%20anew.%20Buildings%20must%20die%2C%20they%20argued%2C%20and%20without%20the%20idea%20of%20death%2C%20architects%20would%20not%20be%20cured%20of%20their%20obsession%20with%20the%20new.%20To%20them%2C%20the%20loss%20of%20buildings%20was%20a%20positive%20thing%20that%20compelled%20a%20rethink%20about%20their%20practice%20and%20the%20lifecycle%20of%20the%20buildings%20they%20construct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArchitects%20may%20not%20entirely%20agree%20with%20this%20provocation%20but%20will%20admit%20that%20their%20practices%20privilege%20%E2%80%98fantasies%20of%20creativity%E2%80%99%20and%20novelty.%C2%A0%20Breaking%20away%20from%20history%20is%20one%20of%20its%20foundational%20ideas%2C%20and%20continuity%20and%20recycling%20are%20anathema.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20architects%E2%80%99%20demand%20to%20perpetuate%20the%20legacy%20of%20modern%20architecture%20by%20presenting%20it%20as%20historical%20seems%20like%20a%20late%20realisation%2C%20if%20not%20an%20irony.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERelated%20to%20this%20is%20the%20perception%20that%20modern%20architecture%20is%20not%20much%20about%20permanence.%20Architects%20position%20buildings%20as%20contained%20spaces%20and%20consider%20function%20as%20the%20key%20driver.%20Modern%20building%20materials%20celebrate%20a%20sense%20of%20lightness%2C%20almost%20bordering%20temporariness.%20If%20the%20pre-modern%20buildings%20were%20about%20permanence%2C%20the%20new%20ones%20are%20transient%20containers%20meant%20to%20be%20demolished%20when%20it%20is%20not%20serving%20their%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20that%20threatens%20the%20building%20value%20is%20the%20land%20value.%20In%20the%20current%20land%20value-driven%20property%20condition%2C%20the%20land%20value%20on%20which%20buildings%20are%20placed%20increases%20rapidly%2C%20which%20can%20be%20extracted%20only%20by%20demolishing%20the%20building.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20building%20use%20value%20is%20less%20important%20than%20its%20exchange%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20UK%20heritage%20policy%20expert%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.academia.edu%2F3639888%2FCapturing_the_Public_Value_of_Heritage%5C%22%3EKate%20Clark%2C%20reframes%20this%20problem%20in%20the%20context%20of%20conservation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20points%20out%20that%20the%20debate%20is%20about%20the%20intrinsic%20and%20instrumental%20values%20of%20a%20building.%20The%20argument%20against%20modern%20architecture%20is%20that%20it%20does%20not%20have%20intrinsic%20public%20value%20and%20should%20be%20judged%20only%20by%20its%20instrumental%20economic%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20to%20rectify%20this%3F%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Farkitekturforskning.net%2Fna%2Farticle%2FviewFile%2F296%2F256%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOn%2520Alois%2520Riegl%2527s%2520Modern%2520Cult%2520of%2520Monuments%26amp%3Btext%3DAge%252C%2520signified%2520through%2520disintegration%252C%2520mani%2Cto%2520appreciate%2520its%2520visual%2520qualities.%5C%22%3EAlois%20Riegl%E2%80%99s%20analysis%20of%20monuments%3C%2Fa%3E%20offers%20help.%20Modern%20buildings%20may%20have%20been%20designed%20to%20serve%20their%20function%20and%20never%20intended%20to%20commemorate%20nor%20have%20traits%20of%20conventional%20monuments.%20However%2C%20they%20could%20become%20%E2%80%98unintentional%20monuments.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReigl%20points%20out%20that%20unintentional%20monuments%20could%20perform%20commemorative%20functions%20as%20the%20intentional%20ones.%20However%2C%20the%20key%20difference%20is%20that%20%E2%80%98while%20the%20value%20of%20the%20intentional%20monument%20is%20always%20conditioned%20by%20its%20makers%2C%20the%20value%20of%20the%20unintentional%20monument%20is%20relative%20and%20left%20to%20us%20to%20define.%E2%80%99%20In%20other%20words%2C%20architects%20have%20the%20biggest%20onus%20to%20define%20the%20value%20of%20modern%20architecture%20to%20save%20it%20from%20demolition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20as%20Kate%20Clark%20would%20argue%2C%20positioning%20conservation%20as%20a%20sustainability%20measure%20would%20help.%20Protecting%20a%20modern%20building%20is%20not%20only%20about%20the%20longevity%20of%20a%20structure.%20Reusing%20or%20adapting%20a%20building%20for%20another%20use%20saves%20the%20energy%20consumed%20in%20producing%20the%20building%20materials%2C%20which%20would%20be%20wasted%20if%20demolished.%20Reuse%20also%20saves%20energy%20consumed%20in%20building%20a%20new%20structure%20in%20place%20of%20the%20existing%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20many%20new%20constructions%2C%20such%20measures%20would%20make%20a%20big%20difference.%20It%20will%20be%20critical%20to%20empirically%20demonstrate%20how%20much%20reuse%20or%20extended%20use%20of%20the%20landmark%20building%20saves%20and%20how%20it%20is%20a%20sound%20environmental%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetrofitting%20or%20repairing%20modern%20architectural%20landmarks%20could%20be%20challenging.%20Concrete%20structures%2C%20as%20in%20the%20Ahmedabad%20Stadium%2C%20are%20challenging%20to%20preserve.%20Glazing%20used%20in%20modern%20buildings%20is%20only%20sometimes%20energy%20efficient.%20Techniques%20and%20knowledge%20needed%20to%20conserve%20fragile%20modern%20materials%20and%20structures%20are%20still%20evolving.%20These%20challenges%20can%20be%20met.%20But%20what%20is%20immediately%20needed%20is%20a%20change%20in%20perception%20about%20the%20value%20of%20modern%20architecture%2C%20how%20we%20assess%20them%2C%20and%20the%20will%20to%20protect%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA.%20Srivathsan%20is%20a%20professor%20at%20CEPT%20University.%20The%20views%20expressed%20are%20personal.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694856621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F03203111%2FSVP-stadium.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fwhy-conserving-modern-architecture-has-become-nearly-impossible%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Retrofitting%20or%20repairing%20modern%20architectural%20landmarks%20could%20be%20challenging.%20Concrete%20structures%2C%20as%20in%20the%20Ahmedabad%20Stadium%2C%20are%20challenging%20to%20preserve.%20Among%20others%2C%20glazing%20used%20in%20modern%20buildings%20is%20only%20sometimes%20energy%20efficient.%20But%20these%20challenges%20can%20be%20met.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fwhy-conserving-modern-architecture-has-become-nearly-impossible%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22First%20meeting%20of%20committee%20on%20simultaneous%20polls%20on%20Sept%2023%3A%20Kovind%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694856068000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Fmisc%2F2022-06%2F06%2Ffull%2Fram-nath-kovind-1654496743-95073100.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Felections%2Flok-sabha-election%2Ffirst-meeting-of-committee-on-simultaneous-polls-on-sept-23-kovind-123091600406_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government%20on%20September%202%20notified%20the%20eight-member%20committee%20to%20examine%20and%20make%20recommendations%20for%20holding%20simultaneous%20elections%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Felections%2Flok-sabha-election%2Ffirst-meeting-of-committee-on-simultaneous-polls-on-sept-23-kovind-123091600406_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fww